---
alwaysApply: true
---

Review this screen/feature as a senior UI engineer.
Context Files - Read before auditing:
- /docs/PRD.md - product requirements
- /styles/tokens.css - design tokens
- /src/components/ui/ - available UI components
Architecture:
- Is Server vs Client component split appropriate?
- Is data fetching at the right level?
- Could logic be extracted into custom hooks?
Component Usage:
- Using design system components instead of raw HTML?
- Consistent with existing codebase patterns?
- Not duplicating existing component library functionality?
Accessibility:
- Focus management on navigation and modal open/close
- Keyboard navigation complete for all interactive elements
- Screen reader announcements for dynamic content
- Proper heading hierarchy (h1 -> h2 -> h3)
Edge Cases:
- Loading states handled with skeletons or spinners
- Error states with user-friendly messages
- Empty states with helpful guidance
- Graceful fallbacks for missing/undefined data
Performance:
- Unnecessary re-renders avoided?
- Heavy computations memoized with useMemo?
- Images optimized with Next.js Image component?
Security (if rendering user content):
- User input sanitized before display
- No dangerouslySetInnerHTML without sanitization
- No sensitive data exposed in client-side code
Propose specific refactors with:
- File paths and line numbers
- Code examples showing the fix
- Priority (critical / recommended / nice-to-have)
- Explanation of why the change matters
